values:
We are all born innocent
with an open trusting mind
our future is wide open
to be determined by experience and time

Some of us will die young
atopped abruptly by the clock
and some will live to be old
even if our memories do not

Which is better, which is worse?
Is this life a blessing, or is it a curse?
one life taken away
knowing they have so much to lose
While another is on life support
and would pull the plug if they could choose

Flip of the coin, roll of the dice
One takes, one gives, one dies, one lives
how much do we have to sacrifice
to win the game that we call life

I love you
so please walk away
So I don't have to see the day
When you look at me and say
Goodbye

I love you
So please just go
Cause I don't want to know
What your kisses feel like cold as snow
Where did the warmth go?
I'd rather be alone
Than try to crawl up from that low

I love you
Let's leave it like that
It's beautiful right where its at
If we give it time, it will crack
The waves in our ocean will go flat
And we won't ever get it back

I love you
can't you see
I can hold us flawless in my memory
And our love will always be perfect to me
I love you forever
Now please
       just leave

Blind
 You are all so blind
 my smile turns into infinite pain
 if you look at it from the inside
 the mask I wear is an illusion
 my eyes may shine
 but behind lies a blank stare
 Im past falling backwards
 Im not going to be ok
 and i no longer care
 my mind is gone
 Im living on autopilot
 It's kinda funny really
 that none of you see it
 I am Queen of self destruct
 and Goddess of "I dont give a fuck"
 I may look like the happiest girl alive
 But Im dying inside
 and I wont try to stop it
 I allow the slow suicide
 I'll even help it
 my illness has beat me
 Im at a dead end
 Ive lost all will to live
 im so fucking sick
 it'll be beautiful when Im dead

Life grabs hold of your every emotion,
Squeezing wretched things from your darkest thoughts,
Every breath you breathe something more dangerous is given to the system,
What system you ask?
That system that keeps you faltering from the greatness you truly could be,
If only your life was not what controlled your breathing,
What controlled your emotion? 
What controlled the dark thoughts that control you?
If no one could feel pain,
Or suffer love,
No one could be, or breathe or carry hate within the wave of revenge,
If life was not given,
Life would not be,
And if life was not in existence,
Neither would the sad sorry hopelessness that runs in your veins,
And powers the love that keeps you moving from the dark,
Keeps you moving away from the wave a vengeance so close to you,
If you depend on others you will only be smothered beneath the icy water that is regret,
Regret that you loved someone who you did not know did not love you,
Regret that you were everything you wanted to be with them,
Regret that you were everything you hated by yourself,
Regret that the love you so desperately wanted,
 Was now tearing you apart limb from limb,
As the life is so hopelessly ripped out of you, 
You feel the light of forgiveness giving you the strength to pull yourself back together and heal the scars that were known for there deep passion for pain,
Only the lies that now hold you together can rip you apart and whoever you trusted with the threads that weave you,
Can break you for good,
Have you taken life and love for granted? Only you will know when the final breath you take is either alone,
Or holding the hand of your maker,
Who makes you whole?
Who keeps you from the verge of death, who keeps you from polishing off those last drops of poison that will bring your downfall?
Your heartbreaker or your life maker?
